i make little program check prime number one time. very fast, much safe.

```rust
fn main() {
    let number = 29;

    if is_prime(number) {
        println!("{} is prime number", number);
    } else {
        println!("{} is not prime number", number);
    }
}

fn is_prime(number: u32) -> bool {
    if number <= 1 {
        return false;
    }

    for i in 2..number {
        if number % i == 0 {
            return false;
        }
    }

    true
}
```

